===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*g-sal||clear, bright, pleasant}} ({{zh-ref|Unger, 1990}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; STEDT). Cognate with {{cog|bo|аҪҰаҪЈајӢаҪ–ајҚ||clear, distinct, bright}}.

{{zh-ref|Benedict, 1972}} compares this with {{cog|bo|аҪҳаҪҡаҪўајӢаҪ–|t=bright, shining, beautiful}} yet this isn't preferrable consider Middle Chinese *''tsК°-'' corresponds to Written Tibetan ''gs-''.

{{zh-ref|Luce, 1981}} considers the "polished white rice" sense to be related to {{cog|my|бҖҶбҖ”бҖә|t=uncooked white rice}}, perhaps referring to the "clear and bright" nature of uncooked rice.

Same word as {{och-l|зҮҰ}}.

